# Terminal Commands and Utilities

This document outlines the custom terminal commands and utilities available in this dotfiles configuration.

## File System Navigation

- `e`: Enhanced directory listing using eza with git integration and icons
- `fd`: Improved find command that excludes system directories
- `storage_usage`: Analyze and display top disk space consumers

## Development Workflows

- `save_cursor_config`: Backs up Cursor IDE settings to dotfiles repository
- `rollback_cursor_config`: Restores Cursor IDE settings from backups
- `save_vsc_config`: Backs up VS Code settings to dotfiles repository

## Git Utilities

- `copy_head_commit_hash`: Copies the current git commit hash to clipboard

## Docker Management

- `kill_all_docker_container`: Removes all Docker containers
- `remove_all_docker_images`: Removes all Docker images

## AWS Configuration

- `awsdir [profile]`: Switch between different AWS profiles:
  - `awsdir laststance`: Switch to LaststanceIO AWS profile
  - `awsdir customer`: Switch to customer AWS profile
  - `awsdir prod`: Switch to production AWS profile

## System Information

- `cpuinfo`: Display CPU and hardware information
- `port_usage`: Show which processes are using which ports
- `wanip`: Get your public IP address

## Media Processing

- `mov2gif`: Convert .mov video files to optimized GIFs
